justification: Photophobia and headache are common migraine symptoms. Aura can manifest as scintillations, dysarthria, and weakness.}, {diagnosis: Transient ischemic attack (TIA)

justification: TIA can cause a combination of neurological symptoms like weakness, dysarthria, and visual disturbances like scintillations. Headache can occur, though less common.}, {diagnosis: Stroke
justification: Similar to TIA but with longer-lasting symptoms, stroke can cause a range of neurological deficits including those listed.}, {diagnosis: Meningitis
justification: Headache, photophobia, and neurological symptoms can be present in meningitis.}, {diagnosis: Encephalitis
justification: Similar to meningitis, encephalitis can cause headache, photophobia, and a range of neurological symptoms.}, {diagnosis: Brain tumor
justification: Depending on location, a brain tumor can cause a variety of symptoms, including headache, visual changes, weakness, and speech difficulties.}, {diagnosis: Multiple sclerosis (MS)

justification: MS can cause a wide range of neurological symptoms, including those mentioned. However, its less likely to present with all these symptoms simultaneously.}, {diagnosis: Posterior reversible encephalopathy syndrome (PRES)
justification: PRES typically presents with headache, visual disturbances, and neurological symptoms. However, dysarthria and weakness are less common.}, {diagnosis: Complicated migraine
justification: This refers to migraines with unusual or prolonged neurological symptoms, which could potentially include the symptoms mentioned.}, {diagnosis: Ocular migraine
justification: While primarily causing visual disturbances like scintillations, ocular migraines can sometimes be accompanied by headache and, rarely, other neurological symptoms.}
